    "summary": "Building on fourteen years of mediating in armed conflict, I am dedicated to helping people and organizations manoeuvre conflict (including that tough negotiation phase). What drives me is contributing to positive change. \n\nSince co-founding the Dialogue Advisory Group in 2008, I have gained solid experience in setting up, developing and successfully managing an organisation with fifteen employees and 15-20 external advisors. In terms of governance experience, I enjoy being a board member in a complex and changing environment.\n\nAs a conflict resolution and negotiation expert I have diverse experience in national and international corporate, government and not-for-profit environments. Between 2008 and 2022, as a peace mediator, I conducted a dialogue with leaders of armed groups with the aim of reducing violence, including in Iraq and the Democratic Republic of Congo. Between 2009 and 2017, I was part of a small team that negotiated the disarmament of armed groups in Northern Ireland and the Basque Country.\n\nI also teach conflict management at the University of Amsterdam and speak publicly and in the media about my expertise. In 2022 my book 'Ontwapend' was published.",
